<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1906,2041]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,151,393]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,359,1906,1933]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The genus includes 38 species (including the nominotypical subspecies) and 2 subspecies distributed mainly in the Oriental region comprising 
<collectingCountry box="[673,733,1943,1969]" name="India" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[745,815,1943,1969]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[826,937,1943,1969]" name="Myanmar" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[948,1053,1943,1969]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1065,1177,1943,1969]" name="Indonesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1188,1283,1943,1969]" name="Vietnam" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1337,1437,1943,1969]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Thailand</collectingCountry>
and with few species in the Australian tropics (
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[684,863,1979,2005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">Holloway 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirti, J. S. &amp; Joshi, R. &amp; Singh, N." box="[875,1062,1979,2005]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" pagination="11 - 19" refId="ref9608" refString="Kirti, J. S., Joshi, R. &amp; Singh, N. (2014) A new species of genus Teulisna Walker (Lepidoptera: Erebidae: Arctiinae) from India. Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia, 57 (1 - 2), 11 - 19. https: // doi. org / 10.3409 / AZC. 57 _ 1 - 2.11" type="journal article" year="2014">
Kirti 
<emphasis box="[936,993,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). The wing shape of the 
<taxonomicName family="Erebidae" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis box="[1342,1436,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Teulisna</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
varies, but broadly categorized into the typical group having the forewing tornus falcate, and the 
<emphasis box="[1360,1436,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">bitecta</emphasis>
group with elongate and elliptical forewing. Majority of the species are sexually dimorphic where males show varying degrees of forewing modifications with the brushes of scales at the base of costa and in the cell. 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[1248,1432,187,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="174 - 271" refId="ref9292" refString="Holloway, J. D. (1982) Taxonomic Appendix. In: Barlow, H. S. (Ed.), An Introduction to the Moths of South East Asia. The Malayan Nature Society, Kuala Lumpur, pp. 174 - 271." type="book chapter" year="1982">Holloway (1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[151,208,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
) identified male genitalia characters typical to the genus including squarish frame of the vinculum, slightly indented at the distal margin, supporting a membrane which often holds diverse setose patches, scent pencils and other structures, saccular process of the valva has dense setae or apical spines and aedeagus vesica has diverticula which may or may not have cornuti. In 
<collectingCountry box="[588,648,331,357]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[659,753,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[659,753,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Teulisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by 11 species, mainly from the North-East and Western Ghats (
<bibRefCitation author="Singh, N. &amp; Joshi, R. &amp; Kirti, J. S. &amp; Bisht, S. S. &amp; Param, H. S." box="[329,539,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="1" refId="ref10678" refString="Singh, N., Joshi, R., Kirti, J. S., Bisht, S. S. &amp; Param, H. S. (2021 e) A catalogue of Indian Arctiinae (Erebidae, Lepidoptera). Zootaxa, 5058 (1), 001 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5058.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Singh 
<emphasis box="[403,460,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
2021e
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
